cdjot-specific tests: bugs found via corpus comparison against JS djot,
plus regression tests for spec-correct behavior that JS djot gets wrong.

Verbatim space stripping applies regardless of delimiter length.
The spec says: "If the content starts or ends with a backtick character,
a single space is removed between the opening or closing backticks and
the content."

```
`` `foo` ``
.
<p><code>`foo`</code></p>
```

```
`` ` ``
.
<p><code>`</code></p>
```

URL line continuation: "the line breaks and any leading and trailing
space is ignored, and the lines are concatenated together."

```
[link](url
  andurl)
.
<p><a href="urlandurl">link</a></p>
```

```
[link](http://example.com?n=123
    456)
.
<p><a href="http://example.com?n=123456">link</a></p>
```

Emphasis precedence: "When there are multiple openers that might be
matched with a given closer, the closest one is used."

```
*not strong *strong*
.
<p>*not strong <strong>strong</strong></p>
```

Nested emphasis: "Emphasis can be nested."

```
__emphasis inside_ emphasis_
.
<p><em><em>emphasis inside</em> emphasis</em></p>
```

```
*a *b* c*
.
<p><strong>a <strong>b</strong> c</strong></p>
```

```
_a _b_ c_
.
<p><em>a <em>b</em> c</em></p>
```

Regression tests: these verify spec-correct behavior that JS djot
(v0.3.2) gets wrong. cdjot already passes these.

The star inside a link destination is protected from closing emphasis:

```
*[closed](hello*)
.
<p>*<a href="hello*">closed</a></p>
```

Underscores in link destinations don't close emphasis:

```
_[link](http://example.com?foo_bar=1), more text_
.
<p><em><a href="http://example.com?foo_bar=1">link</a>, more text</em></p>
```

```
_hello [link](a_b) world_
.
<p><em>hello <a href="a_b">link</a> world</em></p>
```

Block attributes require no blank line before the block:

```
{#id .class}

A paragraph
.
<p>A paragraph</p>
```

Heading auto-ID excludes footnote reference text (spec explicitly
states: "# Introduction[^1] generates the identifier Introduction,
not Introduction1"):

```
# Introduction[^1]

[^1]: A note.
.
<section id="Introduction">
<h1>Introduction<a id="fnref1" href="#fn1" role="doc-noteref"><sup>1</sup></a></h1>
</section>
<section role="doc-endnotes">
<hr>
<ol>
<li id="fn1">
<p>A note.<a href="#fnref1" role="doc-backlink">↩︎</a></p>
</li>
</ol>
</section>
```

Different bullet markers create separate lists:

```
- [ ] foo
+ [ ] bar
* [ ] baz
.
<ul class="task-list">
<li>
<input disabled="" type="checkbox"/>
foo
</li>
</ul>
<ul class="task-list">
<li>
<input disabled="" type="checkbox"/>
bar
</li>
</ul>
<ul class="task-list">
<li>
<input disabled="" type="checkbox"/>
baz
</li>
</ul>
```
